Aim:
To learn how to use lists and perform different operations on lists in Python.

Algorithm:
Start the program.
Create a list with some numbers.
Display the original list.
Add a new element to the list.
Insert an element at a specific position.
Remove an element from the list.
Display the length of the list.
Sort the list and display it.
Stop the program.

Code:
numbers = [10, 20, 30, 40]
print("Original list:", numbers)
numbers.append(50)
print("After adding element:", numbers)
numbers.insert(2, 25)
print("After inserting element:", numbers)
numbers.remove(30)
print("After removing element:", numbers)
print("Length of list:", len(numbers))
numbers.sort()
print("Sorted list:", numbers)

Output:
Original list: [10, 20, 30, 40]
After adding element: [10, 20, 30, 40, 50]
After inserting element: [10, 20, 25, 30, 40, 50]
After removing element: [10, 20, 25, 40, 50]
Length of list: 5
Sorted list: [10, 20, 25, 40, 50]
